// netctl Go workspace.
//
// The repository is a monorepo built around a single primary module
// (github.com/imfeelingtheagi/netctl: cmd/, internal/, pkg/) plus a separate
// integration-test module (./test) whose heavier, test-only dependencies are
// intentionally kept out of the main module's go.mod / go.sum. The workspace
// ties them together for local development and CI; production builds use each
// module's own go.mod. Additional modules (e.g. a future public SDK) can be
// added with `go work use ./<dir>` without disturbing existing imports.
go 1.26

// Pin the build toolchain to a patched Go (stdlib fixes for GO-2026-5037
// crypto/x509 + GO-2026-5039 net/textproto). The `go` line above is the language
// version; this is the minimum toolchain CI and dev builds resolve to.
toolchain go1.26.4

use (
	.
	./test
)
